## Acknowledgements

SuperSpec is built upon the work of two open source projects:

**OpenSpec** (https://github.com/Fission-AI/OpenSpec)
SuperSpec adopts OpenSpec's Delta Spec artifact system, schema-driven artifact
DAG, and change lifecycle (explore → propose → apply → archive). The WHAT/HOW
separation principle and spec evolution cycle are derived directly from OpenSpec's
design philosophy.

**Superpowers** (https://github.com/obra/superpowers)
SuperSpec adopts Superpowers' Iron Law discipline, skill-based workflow
enforcement, subagent-driven development pattern, and verification-before-
completion principle. The three-gear speed control and anti-rationalization
infrastructure are inspired by Superpowers' approach to AI agent reliability.

SuperSpec's contribution is the fusion of these two frameworks: wiring OpenSpec's
persistent spec artifacts as the input and baseline for Superpowers' execution
discipline, such that specs drive implementation, implementation is verified
against specs, and specs evolve cleanly over time.

Both upstream projects retain their respective copyrights and licenses.
Users of SuperSpec should review and comply with the licenses of OpenSpec and
Superpowers as well.
